<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Sir Yakk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>All of this is in a theoretically ideal situation (you have a boss engaged, and are dumping mana into panthering melee)<br />
<br />
Damage Per Cast (DPC) of Panther: (DPS from panther-buff)*Duration<br />
<br />
Panther <b>Cycle Time</b> = Cast Time + <b>Recast Time</b><br />
Panther Cast Time = 3.0 (focus'd by AA) + 2.5 (recovery)<br />
Panther <b>Recast Time</b> = 2.5 (on test, 30)<br />
<br />
Panther Duration = 60 * 1.75 = 105 seconds<br />
<br />
Damage Per Cycle Time (<b>DPCT</b>) from Panther: DPC / (<b>Cycle Time</b>)<br />
Damage Per Second Casting (DPSC) = DPC / (Casting Time + 2.5)<br />
<br />
Damage Per Mana (DPM) from Panther: DPC / 650 (unfocus'd, easier to compare with other classes)<br />
<br />
DPS from panther-buff: About 100 DPS on a player<br />
<br />
<b>Max Burst</b> DPS from Panther: DPS * Duration / <b>Cycle Time</b> = <b>DPCT</b><br />
<br />
So:<br />
DPC: 10.5 k damage per cast of panther<br />
DPCT: 1909 damage per second of cycle time<br />
DPSC: 1909 damage per second of casting time<br />
DPM: 16.15 dam/mana (unfocus'd)<br />
Max Burst: 1909 DPS = DPCT<br />
<br />
Changes on test change the Cycle Time from 5.5 to 33 seconds.<br />
<br />
After changes:<br />
Max Burst = DPCT = 318.17 DPS<br />
<br />
And, it makes it a far more annoying spell to use.<br />
<br />
The max-burst DPS requires an insane amount of mana (Spiritual Channelling and mass-necro-mana feed level of mana).  However, the high DPM means that feeding the shaman mana is worth it: necro mana filtered through a shaman does more damage than used directly.  <br />
<br />
Without any outside active aid:<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />At 120 mana/tick, over a 5 minute fight, with 10 k mana to start with, a shaman could cause 400,000+ damage to be pumped out via casting this buff.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Wizards without outside active aid:<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Wizard's ancient nukes have a raw ratio of 4.8 damage:mana.  A 120 mana/tick wizard with 10.5 k mana who dumps every last drop into the mob does 132,000 damage before crits/damage focus items.<br />
<br />
With +90% damage foci, 30% crit rate, and +30% crit damage (overestimating by enough to leave a compy margin: I believe this is well beyond what a PC can get now), that wizard does 243,000 damage.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>(the above are assuming 40% mana pres from items+SCM+Spec for both shamans and wizards.  A change in mana pres would effect both shamans and wizards equally.)<br />
<br />
Is there any errors in my math?  I am guessing that SOE has done the same math I did above.<br />
<br />
(by "active aid", I mean someone else doing something they would not otherwise do.  Twitch, sing a different song, etc.)</p>
	
	
	
	
	
