<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Sir Yakk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>L 69 shaman with no AA and no gear</b>:<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Damage Per Cast (DPC) of Panther: (DPS from panther-buff)*Duration<br />
<br />
Panther Cycle Time = Cast Time + Recast Time<br />
Panther Cast Time = <b>6.0</b> (<b>un</b>focus'd by AA) + 2.5 (recovery)<br />
Panther Recast Time = 2.5 (on test, 30)<br />
<br />
Panther Duration = 60 * 1.0 = 60 seconds<br />
<br />
Damage Per Cycle Time (DPCT) from Panther: DPC / (Cycle Time)<br />
Damage Per Second Casting (DPSC) = DPC / (Casting Time + 2.5)<br />
<br />
Damage Per Mana (DPM) from Panther: DPC / 650 (unfocus'd, easier to compare with other classes)<br />
<br />
DPS from panther-buff: About 100 DPS on a player (<b>assumes high dex</b>)<br />
<br />
Max Burst DPS from Panther: DPS * Duration / Cycle Time = DPCT<br />
<br />
So:<br />
DPC: <b>6</b> k damage per cast of panther<br />
DPCT: <b>706</b> damage per second of cycle time<br />
DPSC: <b>706</b> damage per second of casting time<br />
DPM: <b>10.0</b> dam/mana (unfocus'd)<br />
Max Burst: <b>706</b> DPS = DPCT <br />
<br />
With 30 second recast:<br />
DPCT=Max Burst=167 DPS<hr size="1" /></blockquote>If you add in a 10 hit count, extended-buff AAs matter less.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Don't forget that in a raid situation, the raid can only take advantage of one shaman that you describe above while any wizard can do that much damage.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Actually, if you don't use necro-twich or spriritual channeling (which is what the 400,000 damage shaman didn't use), each shaman is only keeping it up on at most 16 targets.  3 shamans could 'easily' stack doing this on a raid.<br />
<br />
Alternate to the above solution I liked:<br />
Leave panther/leopard at 1 minute duration, keep proc rate the same.<br />
Set max_proc_number to 10.<br />
Do not add a recast delay.<br />
<br />
This halves the 'perfect situation' (ie, raid) power of this spell, and barely harms the 'non-perfect situation' (non-chain-pull group) power of the spell, and the spell isn't nearly as annoying as having a recast delay on it.<br />
<br />
The spell keeps it's 'burst' power for groups, but it fades after just under 1 minute of combat.  Extended buff AAs and foci allow you to buff before engage and use the 10 procs per buff fully, so are quite useful, but do not up the power of the spell by 75% anymore.<br />
<br />
In other words, shamans start doing less DPS <b>just via casting this spell</b> than a fully geared anguish wizard.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;postid=334438">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;do=getip&postid=334438">Logged</a></div>
	
	<!-- / message -->
		
	</td>
