<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Macnair</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2004<br />
	Location: Halas
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Sir Yakk</b><br /><i>All of this is in a theoretically ideal situation (you have a boss engaged, and are dumping mana into panthering melee)</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>You have some interesting numbers here, Yakk.  <br />
<br />
I think some of your variables provide useful side-numbers, but they don't really figure into the calculations.<br />
<br />
I think some of your numbers are roundoffs and estimates (100 dps for panthered melees instead of 92 dps; guesstimating wizard damage 'with a comfy margin'; and so on).<br />
<br />
You have not factored in efficiency:  a wizard who only has to target the mob one time and then cast the spell will be much more efficient than a shaman who has to target a melee, cast, target another melee, cast.  The shaman will lose many small fractions of time along the way.<br />
<br />
You have not factored in that the shaman's dps takes half of the fight to build to full, while the wizard's is constant across the three minutes.<br />
<br />
If we are trying to calculate the max burst damage <i>possible</i> over a 3 minute fight, then I think mana calculations are not a factor:  we will simply line up however many necros we need, to pump however much mana is lacking, to achieve this maximum.<br />
<br />
<b>What would a wizard's max burst dps be, over 3 minutes?</b><br />
<br />
I freely admit I am pretty ignorant about wizard stuff, so I went to Graffe's and read spell info and commentary from the forums there.  At a first cut (please please some of you knowledgeable people come up with better analysis):<br />
<br />
It appears that with maximum aa and focii, and the proper buffs, a wizard can chain cast the spell "Ancient: Core Fire" 23 times in 3 minutes.  Assuming that the tank can hold aggro like superglue, that the mob is fully debuffed, assuming 18 nukes land for full @ 7936, while 5 crit @ 12006 damage:  202,878 total damage = 1127 dps.  Assuming 98% efficiency (nobody is perfect):  1104 max burst dps.<br />
<br />
<b>What would a shaman's max burst dps be, over 3 minutes?</b><br />
<br />
In the other thread I calculated shaman max burst dps at 1113.<br />
<br />
If that is correct so far (I'm counting on people to provide better wizard numbers), that would make the two essentially equal, for max theoretical burst dps.  (I'm sure there is error built in at the moment; the difference of 9 dps is inconsequential within that margin of error.)<br />
<br />
Now, these situations are not normal.  We don't set up raids in order to maximize wizards dps; we don't set up raids in order to maximize shaman dps.  These are only calculations of what <i>might</i> be possible, if we were to stack the deck in order to maximize the dps of one character.<br />
<br />
I'll offer three preliminary conclusions.<br />
<br />
First, even though these are theoretical numbers rather than numbers you would get in ordinary practice, people at SOE will consider that a shaman should not in theory be able to match a wizard's max burst dps.<br />
<br />
Second, the wizard's theoretical burst dps comes from the wizard chain nuking the target boss mob.  The shaman's theoretical burst dps comes from chain buffing 18 other characters, who then actually cause the damage.  The wizard's dps is direct; the shaman's is cooperative.  That means that a straight comparison might not be appropriate:  it is comparing apples to oranges.<br />
<br />
Third, some sort of decision needs to be made as to what level of cooperative dps is the maximum that we think a shaman should be able to provide.  If a shaman can buff 18 people to provide an additional 1000 dps, is that all right?  800? 600?  What level of cooperative dps is acceptable to be accomplished with shaman buffs?<br />
<br />
(As an aside.  If you have 30 active melee characters on a raid -- warrior monk rogue paladin shadowknight ranger berserker beastlord beastpet magepet necropet -- who provide an average of 150 dps while fighting <i>unhasted</i>:  then one enchanter casting one (!!) mgb 70% haste provides 3150 cooperative dps for the next hour.  Assuming that that's zero while we are moving or standing around, and that during trash pulls we are sloppy, but during a three minute boss fight we are all pretty attentive:  we will claim 75% efficiency during the three minute boss fight.  The enchanter's cooperative dps during that fight -- off of a buff cast 40 minutes ago -- is 2362 dps.  More than the wizard's and the shaman's theoretical max combined.  And that's a real number that would show up in any raid, not a theoretical one calculated off of trying to figure out what's the max possible.)</p>
	
	
	
