<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Oracle<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>This game has too many classes, half of which regard themselves as "the damage class" and the other half of which want to "at least do decent damage" which usually translates to "I want to do at least 70% of what a DPS class does". The only solution I can see is to diversify damage. And since we do not want to make classes useless in experience grouping there is only direct vs indirect damage and burst DPS vs steady DPS to work with.<br />
<br />
Indirect damage is haste and the likes. This will have to be strictly more efficient then direct DPS, since you can not indefinitely stack it. How much better? That is anyone's guess. But in the case of panther you can play with the DPS of a single panther spell and the duration of the spell, in addition to the usual DPS/DPM values. So if you raise the impact of a single cast of panther high enough it need not be much more efficient then direct DPS at all.<br />
<br />
As for the "int casters need some loving" bit - yep. But whats more, they need restructuring. Chaincasting nukes is not very different from chainmeleeing at all, and thus they have to be pretty equal in terms of burst DPS - remember, everyone wants to be the definite DPS class. And that means casters lose out with equal DPS (because of their limited mana pool) and melees lose out with less DPS (since they are not the DPS class anymore). Solution? Hand out bigger nukes. Much bigger. Wizards should be nuking for 50K. Yes, 50K. Have it take a third or what not of their mana. I can remember noticing every wizard nuke by watching the target's HPs. Nowadays the only difference between DPS classes seems to be which utility spells they bring to the table. The method of delivering damage does not matter at all. And that sucks. We do not need 10 DPS classes who all want to do the exact same burst and long term DPS. Diversifying them is the first step towards having them all contribute equally, yet differently.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><div align="center">Murtak Gruesome<br />
Prophet of War on Veeshan (retired)<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank">Cestus Dei</a></div></div>
	
	
