	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I got some real easy math.<br />
<br />
 6sec casting time + 30 sec refresh = dead spell<br />
<br />
Hypthetical  instances of  "what a shaman can do with panther" don't work in this game, it's too dynamic. Your assuming that a shaman could effectively keep track of who/who's pet, he/she hit with panther on raid which is not going to happen unless Commander Data from Star Trek is playing EQ. Most raid shamans don't have the luxury of going into "full panther burn" because of the other duties that are required on raids. Hitting the "theoretical Maxium" is like winning the lotto. It could potentially happen but most likely will not.<br />
<br />
The best way I see to fix panther is to do a considerable amount of parsing and adjust the spell on a mana to damage ratio comparable to the damage we can do with our other spells, rather than cast/recast times. Once that is done adjust pet procs to fall in line to the same rate that the spell works on player characters. Then let the shaman community decide if the spell is worth the mana cost or not. By this time Sony shold have a clue on what the spell is capable of in most situations and balance it properly instead of pulling this last minute patch crap.</p>
	
	
	
