</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Not trying to be a smartass, but I promise you that the comparison to haste will not convince any developer to side with you.<br />
<br />
300 DPS is the number he wishes a shaman to achieve.  You can negotiate the number a little bit, perhaps up to 400, but what you should focus on is how can he best tweak the spell so it reaches a maximum DPS figure of around 300 DPS while not being a huge pain in the ass to mantaiin.<br />
<br />
You also have to figure, that even though you can do 300 DPS with DoT, Panther has all sorts of advantages.  Panther requires less time focus'ing on dott'ing and less spell slots taken up.  Panther is aggro free.  Panther works on mobs that are immune to DoT.  Panther is unresistable.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
